Package net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.primitive.ints

Functions that have specialized int-valued type parameters or return types where a throwable may be thrown.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ThrowingIntFunction1<R>
    Represents a function that accepts an int-valued argument and produces a result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingToIntFunction0
    Represents a function that accepts no arguments and produces an int-valued result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingToIntFunction1<T1>
    Represents a function that accepts one argument and produces an int-valued result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingToIntFunction2<T1,T2>
    Represents a function that accepts two arguments and produces an int-valued result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingToIntFunctionN
    Represents a function that accepts n arguments and produces an int-valued result or throws a throwable.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ThrowingToIntFunctionN.Instance
    An instance of ToIntFunctionN which properly defines the arity of that particular function.
